1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes two PSTNN-based minimization models for tensor recovery problems, which involve optimization and machine learning techniques. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions the tensor principal component analysis, which is a common technique in computer vision and image processing. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the recovery of multi-dimensional imaging data, which can be related to information theory and signal processing. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes algorithms based on the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) to solve the proposed PSTNN-based tensor recovery models, which can be related to numerical analysis. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new metric, the partial sum of the tubal nuclear norm (PSTNN), which can be related to data structures and algorithms for tensor analysis.
